<title type="html"><![CDATA[A html5 zoom interface]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=4223&amp;p=5632#p5632"><![CDATA[
Firefox has a nice Zoom function (ctrl+/-). Could such a feature be part of HTML5? Programs like flash (scale entire movieclip) and Air have these possibilities. <br />It would be nice to be able to zoom a div with all it's contents without having to adjust font sizes, image sizes, line-heights etc. Just like the FF zoom works for the whole page.<br />For example <a href="http://www.wired.com/epicenter/2010/02/the-wired-ipad-app-a-video-demonstration/" class="postlink">wired.com</a> has a video about their tablet-app and the digital publishing trend (ipad,e-readers,iphone etc). <br />At 00:50 - 00:53 / 2:08 - 2:18 there is a 'zoom' moment, currently this can not be done with non-canvas / svg elements in HTML5 if i am not mistaken.<br />Would this be a good feature for HTML5?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=692">timvanoostrom</a> — Wed Feb 17, 2010 12:01 pm</p><hr />
